codex
Top infra task from the queue and latest logs was still the security audit for external `udp/5353` mDNS exposure. I hardened the workspace-managed remediation path rather than touching live `/etc` from this sandbox.

- [tools/infra_network.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_network.py:44) now supports override paths for `resolved.conf`, `resolved.conf.d`, and `nsswitch.conf`, checks drop-in mode drift, and emits a safe staging command in the audit output.
- [tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py:35) now has `--install-to` plus validation-path overrides, so the managed drop-in can be staged and verified end-to-end in a temp tree before any privileged host install.
- Added regression coverage in [tests/test_infra_network.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_network.py:17) and [tests/test_infra_mdns_hardening.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_mdns_hardening.py:15).

Verification passed:
- `python3 -m py_compile tools/infra_network.py tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py tools/infra-status.py tools/infra-autopilot.py`
- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_network tests.test_infra_mdns_hardening -v` (`4` tests, all green)
- `python3 tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py --write-managed-dropin` rewrote the managed drop-in at mode `0644`
- Temp staging run installed and validated a drop-in at mode `0644`
- Fresh infra run at `2026-03-08 11:34 UTC` produced [departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260308T113440Z-r15-run-security-audit-check-for-open-ports-ssh-config-faile.md](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260308T113440Z-r15-run-security-audit-check-for-open-ports-ssh-config-faile.md), which now shows the managed asset as ready and includes the stage/test workflow

The live host risk is still open: `/etc/systemd/resolved.conf.d/99-openclaw-no-mdns.conf` is missing, so `udp/5353` remains exposed until that drop-in is installed and `systemd-resolved` is restarted outside this sandbox.
