codex
Picked `Run security audit` as the top infra task. Today’s TODO and latest logs/artifacts kept pointing at external `udp/5353` mDNS exposure as the highest recurring security issue, so I hardened the repo-side remediation workflow around that path.

The main fix is in [tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py#L51) and [tools/infra_network.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_network.py#L102): staged validation no longer claims a `/tmp` drop-in is live. Staged runs now print `Validation target: staged`, report `staged drop-in installed`, and end with `STAGED_VALIDATION_DONE`; real host verification is the only path that should emit `LIVE_VALIDATION_DONE`. I updated the guidance text and tests in [tests/test_infra_mdns_hardening.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_mdns_hardening.py) and [tests/test_infra_network.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_network.py), and recorded the sprint in [departments/infra/MEMORY.md](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/departments/infra/MEMORY.md) and [memory/2026-03-08.md](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-08.md).

Verification passed:
- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_network tests.test_infra_mdns_hardening`
- `python3 -m py_compile tools/infra_network.py tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py tools/infra-autopilot.py tools/infra-status.py`
- `python3 tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py --stage-dir /tmp/openclaw-mdns-stage --validate-live`
- `python3 tools/infra-status.py`
- `python3 tools/department-commands.py run infra`

Fresh checks are in [departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260308T133410Z-infra-status.md](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260308T133410Z-infra-status.md) and [departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260308T133409Z-r20-run-security-audit-check-for-open-ports-ssh-config-faile.md](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260308T133409Z-r20-run-security-audit-check-for-open-ports-ssh-config-faile.md). The live host issue is still present because installing `/etc/systemd/resolved.conf.d/99-openclaw-no-mdns.conf` and restarting `systemd-resolved` require root privileges, which I couldn’t use in this sandboxed session.
