**Result**

Top infra task from `departments/infra/TODO.md` plus the latest infra logs/artifacts was still `Run security audit`, driven by repeated external `udp/5353` exposure. I hardened the repo-side remediation flow instead of touching `/etc`.

In [tools/infra_network.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_network.py#L25), external mDNS detection now ignores loopback-only `:5353` listeners, and the guidance now distinguishes staged validation from real host remediation. In [tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py#L178), `--validate-live` now fails closed with `LIVE_VALIDATION_FAILED` unless the managed live drop-in is actually installed and `udp/5353` is no longer externally exposed; staged runs end with `STAGED_VALIDATION_READY`. In [tools/infra-status.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra-status.py#L379), the mDNS check now consumes raw socket lines instead of the summarized open-port alert, so the report can’t contradict itself. I also added regression coverage in [tests/test_infra_status.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_status.py#L16), plus updates to the existing mDNS tests.

**Verification**

- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_network tests.test_infra_mdns_hardening tests.test_infra_status` passed (`17` tests).
- `python3 -m py_compile tools/infra_network.py tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py tools/infra-status.py tools/infra-autopilot.py` passed.
- `python3 tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py --stage-dir /tmp/openclaw-mdns-stage --validate-live` ended with `STAGED_VALIDATION_READY`.
