+## 2026-03-08 16:33 UTC — Infra mDNS guidance hardened for non-standard listener owners
+- Reconfirmed from `departments/infra/TODO.md`, `logs/infra-activity.log`, and runs 28-29 that `Run security audit` remains the top unresolved infra task because external `udp/5353` is still exposed.
+- Hardened the repo-side mDNS remediation path again:
+  - `tools/infra_network.py` now parses visible `udp/5353` process owners and flags non-standard owners outside `systemd-resolved` / `avahi-daemon`
+  - mDNS findings now state that the managed resolved drop-in is only defense-in-depth when another service owns the socket, and they tell the operator to inspect/reconfigure that service instead of assuming the drop-in alone is sufficient
+  - `tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py --validate-live` now emits an owner-specific failure when `udp/5353` persists behind a non-standard service
+- Added regression coverage in `tests/test_infra_network.py` and `tests/test_infra_mdns_hardening.py` for the owner-aware path.
+- Verification:
+  - `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_network tests.test_infra_mdns_hardening tests.test_infra_status` passed (`19` tests)
