+## 2026-03-08 17:34 UTC — Infra mDNS owner attribution hardened with PID-aware guidance
+- Reconfirmed from `departments/infra/TODO.md`, `logs/infra-activity.log`, and fresh status/todo output that `Run security audit` remained the top infra task, still driven by recurring external `udp/5353` exposure.
+- Hardened the repo-side remediation path again:
+  - `tools/infra_network.py` now resolves visible `udp/5353` listener owners through `/proc/<pid>/cmdline` when `ss` exposes a PID, so kernel-truncated names like `openclaw-gatewa` can be normalized back to `openclaw-gateway`
+  - mDNS findings now surface visible listener PIDs and tell the operator to inspect the owning process with `ps -fp <pid>` before assuming the `systemd-resolved` drop-in can clear the live listener
+  - `tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py --validate-live` now includes the same PID-aware inspection command in owner-specific failure output
+- Added regression coverage in `tests/test_infra_network.py` and `tests/test_infra_mdns_hardening.py` for truncated-owner normalization and PID-aware guidance.
+- Verification:
+  - `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_network tests.test_infra_mdns_hardening tests.test_infra_status` passed (`19` tests)
+  - `python3 -m py_compile tools/infra_network.py tools/infra_mdns_hardening.py tools/infra-status.py tools/infra-autopilot.py` passed
