The top infra task was `Monitor disk usage`, not mDNS. `departments/infra/TODO.md` and `logs/infra-activity.log` both point to repeated disk-pressure runs, and fresh infra runs 60-61 still report `/` at `100%` used.

I hardened the repo-side disk tooling instead of doing risky live cleanup. In [tools/infra_disk.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_disk.py#L30), high-pressure reports now separate reclaimable caches from protected install roots, so heavy paths like `~/.npm-global`, `~/.android-sdk`, `~/.local/share/pipx/venvs`, and `~/.local/share/claude/versions` are explicitly marked manual-review-only. In [tools/infra_home_cache_cleanup.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_home_cache_cleanup.py#L17), `~/.npm` is now allowlisted as a safe npm download cache for future review/apply cleanup. Regression coverage was added in [tests/test_infra_disk.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_disk.py#L103) and [tests/test_infra_home_cache_cleanup.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_home_cache_cleanup.py#L90).

Verification passed:
- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_disk tests.test_infra_home_cache_cleanup tests.test_infra_status`
