codex
Top infra task from `departments/infra/TODO.md` and `logs/infra-activity.log` was still `Monitor disk usage`, driven by root `/` staying at `100%` used. I attempted the repo’s safe allowlisted cache cleanup path first, but every target failed with `Permission denied` in this session. I hardened the tooling instead so it now fails closed: [tools/infra_home_cache_cleanup.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_home_cache_cleanup.py) does a temporary write probe per cache path and suppresses `--apply` when the current session cannot actually delete there, and [tools/infra_disk.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tools/infra_disk.py) carries that into the disk report/recovery plan as explicit `Apply blocked from current session` guidance instead of advertising a bogus fix. I added regression coverage in [tests/test_infra_home_cache_cleanup.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_home_cache_cleanup.py) and [tests/test_infra_disk.py](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/tests/test_infra_disk.py).

Verification passed with `python3 -m unittest tests.test_infra_home_cache_cleanup tests.test_infra_disk tests.test_infra_status`, `python3 -m py_compile tools/infra_home_cache_cleanup.py tools/infra_disk.py tools/infra-status.py tools/infra-autopilot.py tools/infra_tmp_cleanup.py`, `python3 tools/infra_home_cache_cleanup.py --path ...`, and a fresh `python3 tools/department-commands.py run infra`. The new artifact at [departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260309T174243Z-r69-monitor-disk-usage-alert-if-80.md](/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/departments/infra/artifacts/checks/20260309T174243Z-r69-monitor-disk-usage-alert-if-80.md) now correctly shows review-only cache targets, the blocked apply paths, and that `/` is still `100%` used with about `144MB` free. The remaining operational fix has to be run from a shell with write access to those home-cache directories, and host-level reclaim is still needed to get back under `<=80%`.
